              <span id="reviewTextContainer173596519" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7878646401936885760">This story is very engaging. A pager turner-- I&apos;ve read other books on Communist China--(and the author did an excellent job with getting our emotions fired up by the end of the book with the awful things Mao was responsible for)<br/>but the main plot about Joy running to China to find her father AND &apos;save&apos; her MotherLand&apos; (save China) --- was a little hard to believe. -------yet----I enjoyed the RIDE of the story---(just couldn&apos;t buy it all)....Not the FICTION parts of the book. (which is what can h</span>
  <span id="freeText7878646401936885760" style="display:none">This story is very engaging. A pager turner-- I've read other books on Communist China--(and the author did an excellent job with getting our emotions fired up by the end of the book with the awful things Mao was responsible for)<br />but the main plot about Joy running to China to find her father AND 'save' her MotherLand' (save China) --- was a little hard to believe. -------yet----I enjoyed the RIDE of the story---(just couldn't buy it all)....Not the FICTION parts of the book. (which is what can happen in Historical Fiction). <br /><br /><br />How does a 19 year old Chinese American girl ---educated at American University ---(lived in the United Stated here ENTIRE life)---*really* feel THAT strong about Communist China?</span>
